caption: Cute little place. We enjoyed to the food very much.
Entered near nine, it wasn't busy. I've had nothing but great experiences here and will keep coming back. Food and atmosphere reminds me of Kansas City.
Great spot in downtown Louisville for a coffee or a quick bite to eat.

Chocolate espresso cake. Bourbon molasses cookies. Key lime pie bites. All the energy expended teaching H2O Aerobics this a.m. replaced with creamy tomato soup dotted with homemade toasted croutons. Roasted potato frittata for protein. Sunergos coffee provided the perfect accompaniment for dessert, which I ate first. Beautifully renovated Old Louisville architecture. Definitely a return-to spot.

Yummy food at a good price! The employees are always very friendly and efficient. If you have dietary restrictions, they are also able to answer questions to accommodate your needs. This is a great, local downtown lunch spot.
This place is adorable and they serve healthy food.
I work here and the people and service are amazing, and the food is very tasty but and don't get me started on the desserts.
Good coffee.
I like me an occasional slice of a vegetarian frittata with a bowl of soup. Oh, and don't leave without trying a slice of their key lime pie 🙂

The food is amazing but the service is not. I've ate here about 5 times and every time I've had to wait 30 minutes to get my order of a half sandwich and a salad. Lunch by that time is over. So, order online.
Nice and convenient spot. Turkey sandwich was nice, good prices.
Great low key place! Delicious food and very friendly staff. Has been a great place to eat/work from during my stay here.  Plenty of seating and good WiFi.
Their coffee and breakfast are great
Great coffee, great space to enjoy friends with a tasty snack.
Quick healthy lunch in a great atmosphere.
Nice breakfast selection. Not from the South but enjoyed the biscuit sandwich and the fruit plate. Great latte and the outdoor seating was great ambiance and people-watching in a cool downtown vibe.
Good for quick bite
One of My favorites place !

I came in on a Wednesday at 11am for lunch.  I really wanted to like this place.  The people and the environment are amazing and the service was fast.  As i waited for my food, i imagined myself coming back here multiple times in the future...but then the food came.  I got a tuna sandwich and a  specialty salad.  They were not good and not bad.  It was just blah.  For the price, i expected much more.  The tuna was bland and dry.  The salad was nothing special.  Ill return in the future and try again.  Ill update my review if i have a different experience.

Great food and nice to see (often times) GF options. Great coffee and beverages. Only hang up is that for an establishment where many professionals come and meet and order drinks and food there is no place to pre bus your table. The staff refused to pre bus dishes or plates or even accept them when I brought them up that take up. They said they'll take care of it when you leave. But I'm still meeting and conducting business with dishes in our way. An unecessary inconvenience. Overall, good.
Great place for lunch. Excellent food and lightening fast.
wonderful restaurant to experience  - nice sit out table and interior designs - creamy corn soup was very good - vegetarian sandwich with chips - made my day
Always good!

I met my friend here for lunch. Great little lunch bistro on Main Street   The handsome little counter guy had a smile for us and his patience with me as a first timer there was admirable. Soup and salad? Soup and sandwich? What to get?  My friend works in the building next door and suggested that we get a variety of items and split everything. Good call!  Everything was tasty and fresh and homemade and healthyish. I just joined the gym across the street and I was really happy when I realized that this place is directly across the street.  I’ve been in several times just to grab a beverage. It’s easy to bounce in and out. Comfortable daytime atmosphere. Chill employees.  Need a recommendation for lunch when visiting the Kentucky Center, The KMAC museum or 21c?  Here it is.  Family friendly if that’s your thing and friendly if it isn’t. I really like this place. I’ll get myself back in there to shoot a few photos of their food because it really is a pretty little plate.  Check it out.
Great Mediterranean salad w tuna.
Cute Café that boasts locally sourced ingredients and healthy food options; located in the heart of the business district. It features a rotating menu of quick bites and beverages.
Great place for a good cup of coffee, lunch, or a snack. One of the best downtown Louisville meeting places. Great staff!
One of my favorite lunch spots downtown. Be adventurous and try one of their daily specials, I have eaten there several times and have yet to be dissatisfied.
Great food

Looking for a health change, they had a great selection of vegetarian food. I had an amazing veggie Taco Salad which wasn't wanting for anything. As a meat eater, I didn't miss it, and the flavor was amazing. Great lunch spot, and family friendly.
Great menu choices! Ended up with a cup of tomato basil soup! Screamed fresh! The taste was wonderful, served with croutons and side of crostini. Hit the spot!
Love this place. Great for breakfast & lunch!

Great power salad. Grab a stool in the front window and people watch! Ate there again today. Half salad with soup or half sandwich is very popular choice. Get there before noon, a line forms out the door. Lunch for two was $23.00 including a 1.50 tip for counter service.
The food is delicious, the service gracious and the cookies are as if my granny were back in the kitchen.
Horrible service ! Food was dry and unseasoned plus the food tasted unoriginal and store bought!  was greeted by a very snobby lady with brown hair . I will never go back.
What do u know about them OatmealCream pies!!🔥🔥🔥!! Is all I gotta say!!
Great coffee! Great atmosphere!

I am never disappointed with the food selection, quality of food and amazing customer service from Atlantic No. 5. If you are downtown and looking for a place to eat for lunch I will always recommend this place. They offer a wide range of food for those that are watching what they eat. Vegetarian friendly. The best part of my dining experience are the made from scratch deserts. In my opinion the deserts are better then nearly all bakeries in Louisville. You need to check it out if you haven't already.
Really great spot for coffee and light eats. Nice service, awesome ambiance.

Had the breakfast frittata for lunch. It was marvelous with side of fruit & a Coke in a bottle. Portion large enough to save some for weekend breakfast. Next time I'll have the soup & grilled cheese I actually went for. It looked delicious. Only downside, I would have liked Cafe staff to notice we needed to-go boxes instead of having to ask. Seating is limited as they do a brisk business.
Nice Breakfastplace ! Not too expensive and the quality is good!!
Great food & coffee
This the best place downtown to have breakfast or lunch!
YUM!! I had the egg & avocado on brioche and it was delicious!! The perfect breakfast sandwich. Nice casual, clean spot for coffee and breakfast.
Excellent food at a good price.
Perfect, light breakfast spot.
Chicken salad sandwich was great and service was quick! Fruit fruit salad wasn’t too great though
It's a little cramp during the lunch rush but the food definitely makes it worth it. Try the cookies, they're delicious. My favorite is the bourbon sandwich cookie.
Good space to meet some friends and tasty coffee !
Great little lunch/brunch place! Fantastic staff and food
Good menu
Breakfast was sooooo good. Staff was friendly. The bacon, egg and cheese biscuit was just awesome.
The food is good and atmosphere is very nice the people are also very friendly.
Nice little lunch spot. A bit on the expensive side but the food is good and so is the coffee.
Love the atmosphere here. And great coffee that actually tastes coffee in US. The breakfast options are affordable and fresh. More europe styled breakfast than american.
Food isn't great and way overpriced
Perfect portions 👌🏾

*** VEGETARIAN OPTIONS *** I came here for a work lunch, and was very impressed. I think the amount of food was sufficient enough for a lunch portion. It wasn’t as cheap as fast food, but the fold is significant better. Cute interior, and good atmosphere for a networking lunch with up to 4 people. The location is very convenient to a lot of downtown offices as well.
Great food, friendly people.

This place is my absolute favorite lunch spot downtown! They have the best chocolate chip cookies I've ever tasted!!! This place gets pretty crowded, and there isn't a whole lot of seating, so get there closer to 11am or later like 1pm to beat the lunch rush. The decor is to DIE for. I can't say enough about this place. Get you some lunch - you won't be disappointed. But don't forget the cookie, or any baked goods they have on display that day.
Great establishment with great service!
It’s time. This place needs to close. 100% ORDER FAILURE. ALL OF THEM. Every order has been wrong. I have never seen such a thing. Please close.
Food and service is excellent!  Had The Mediterranean Tuna Salad.  Excellent choice!  Will definitely be back to A 5.
Lovely staff and great food. What a great place for workshops. They really take good care of you.
Great service, food was great and price was average for a cafe in downtown Louisville! ❤ it!
Great food interesting place.

Awesome little coffee shop, good food options, excellent decor, and they usually play good music. Lots of seating, the only reason I'm getting it for stars because there's been a few times or every once in a while the service wasn't as great as I could have hoped for
Excellent service and great breakfast sandwich.
Nice looking interior. Lots of food options offered. Food tasted great. It's a good place for a meeting or to get some work done.
The woman that took my order was very nice.  The rest of the staff looked at my crying child and I like we had three heads. Get over it. Babies cry

I am going to agree with other reviewers. Cute place, good food, friendly staff, but the portions are just too small.  I had a frittata that was wonderful but a tiny triangle. The scone was fab but also smaller. My husband had the baguette sandwich, which was only half. Coffee was good and strong  The place is bright and open with lots of treats specially placed to catch your eye. Staff are happy and it shows.
Nothing special.  Small portion.  Ordered a baguette only to find out it was a half one.

Awesome little spot for a quick lunch.  I was in town for business and had just visited the Louisville Slugger museum.  A short walk away was this little gem.  Cute little location with a great variety of food, coffee, and baked goods.  Turkey sandwich was great!
So delicious!!! So many options for food and drink.  Healthy alternatives and just a beautiful presentation all around.  Won't be disappointed.
Nice spot to grab a bite
Always prefer local businesses and here is a perfect one!

I'd give Atlantic a higher rating, however, I was disappointed with their portion sizes.  The food is tasty, don't get me wrong, there just isn't enough of it for the price.  Perhaps it's my American tendencies, but if I'm paying $10+ for a sandwich and a side, I'd like the size to come in something larger than a condiment cup.  Which may sound like an exaggeration, but I could fit the entire pasta salad in the palm of my hand, with the lid on.  They do brew Sunergos Coffee, which is a huge plus, and their baked goods are worth coming back for.  Although I prefer to eat lunch else where, I do come back regularly for their no-baked cookies, which are larger than a chalkboard eraser.  Honestly, the atmosphere is quaint.  If you're a guy wanting to take a gal out for an afternoon lunch date, she will more than likely enjoy Atlantic No. 5.  oh, and they usually have decent music playing.
I only had a biscuit and espresso but I liked the place. Sat outside and had a business meeting. Good service. Recommend trying the place out.

Desserts on point. I also LOVE their biscuits for breakfast. They brew sunergos coffee here which is strong and delicious. I usually get their iced coffee special. The recently had a Swedish iced coffee that was amazing.
Wonderful homemade biscuits! Coffee was pretty good too.
Great food for dinner or lunch.
This little spot has become my go to lunch spot
Always delicious!
Food was good service was fast.
Fast, friendly, fresh. And reasonably priced. So good.
A5 is a solid option for breakfast and lunch options. The service is usually good, the food is tasty, and the prices are appropriate. If you like bright and clean aesthetics, you'll like A5.
In my one visit, the counter service was friendly and efficient, and my sandwich was tasty.

If you've ever worked in the food industry/retail, or had to bear with a hungry magnate of industry like myself, you can tell pretty quickly that these ladies care. I'm always surprised by the new creations in the pastry case and can always rely on consistent and delicious staples. As far as grilled cheese is concerned, its a little on the pricey side. But as far as grilled cheese is concerned, its some of the best, and my go-to lunch on an overcast Monday afternoon. And these women are as authentic as the real food they make. Sometimes the line is too long, especially now as Summer is on its last leg, and the tourists are finishing up. I made the mistake of going to to the sub shop next door. It was faster and cheaper, but largely artificial. Ended up feeling like I was being driven thru a depressing sustenance factory. Nothing against the staff at the sub shop down the way, I know from experience that its not easy to assemble the same gaunt meat and bagged veggies all day for minimal tips from folks in a hurry. But once again if you've ever had to serve people in a hurry...I was once 20 years old. Dunkin Donuts Class of 2005, PIC (person in charge) from 3-7, M-F Rt 24 North, Bridgewater, MA 02324.  Go to Atlantic No.5 and be thankful you can get real lunch, relatively fast, but unrushed and real on your busy Monday.  #A5SuperFan
Great healthy lunch options and great cookies
Good quality food
Great food Great service
This is always a great spot for lunch. They have tons of different sandwiches and salads. Delicious sweets too! I popped by for breakfast one morning and my ham biscuit was amazing!
Neat atmosphere, friendly service. Unique spin on grilled cheese, very good!
It's unique
Service was great
Breakfast biscuits are the best

Everything here is delicious. The space itself is light and homey and everything I wished my Old Louisville kitchen looked like. Best latte in the city, too. Go ahead and get a dessert. You won't be sorry you did.
My go-to lunch place.  It's delicious!
Love this place! I make a trip every time I'm in Louisville. Friendly staff and great food. The chocolate chip cookies are awesome! They go quick!
Food is great! Service fast and friendly. Atmosphere is perfect!
Friendly service.

Great vibe, excellent coffee and neat "stuff". They had a nice menu and knowledgeable staff. The baked goods were an eclectic offering of French themed and locally sourced goods... Everything you would look for in a downtown coffee shop.
Upscale and trendy sandwich shop with seating inside and out. Good coffee.
Love this place! Coffee is great, good is great and creative. Staff is very friendly. A little slow but that is because they are actually making your food. Highly recommended.
Consistently good food and coffee.
Nice place but please please please turn the music down. I met someone there to talk but the background noise was too much.

This place is addicting. I eat here way too much but I love it all. I haven't had a bad lunch. Make sure you check their social media for daily specials like bahn mi, cuban press and more.....it's all delicious. Their Powerhouse salad is the best salad i've had anywhere and their balsamic dressing is like crack. lol

I was excited to find another downtown restaurant with an app that lets me order ahead and pick up without waiting on line. And they had some delicious looking salads on their menu.  So I ordered their $9 Powerhouse salad and was terribly disappointed. It was the tiniest salad I've ever bought, and there wasn't a single piece of squash in it. I'll never go back.  I can get twice the lunch for the same price around the corner at Panera.

Fancy lunch place with sandwiches, salads, soup.  Don't bother looking at the menu; order out of case and ask for the best looking side to go with it.  Vegetarian options are typically better than the meat options, and most of the meat options are still very tasty.  Sweet tea made perfectly: not too bitter and not too sweet.  Also note the habanero spicy pickles.  Best pickles I have ever tasted.
Food is good, though pricey. Plan on a wait during lunch - they get slammed!
This place is a great little gem. Much better for your morning coffee and pastry than anything else in Louisville and hands down over that big national chain.
Great food and wonderful atmosphere and aesthetic! It almost feels like you're in someone's kitchen. The food is fresh and tastes great!
The menu is one of a kind.
Great staff and superb food. The simple industrial aesthetics are warm and inviting and the food is exciting and fresh. Do yourself a favor...

There's a saying that if you are in a city for the first time and you are looking for food, just go to where there are a line of locals and you will be fine. Atlantic No. 5 fits this to a tee.  I can't believe this place has gotten several reviews and none of them have mentioned the baked goods. Nothing beats fresh baked - incredibly flaky, warm and comforting! My favorite breakfast & lunch spot in Louisville. The biscuits are huge, moist and flaky. And they get one little thing right that most restaurants can't be bothered with: make it fresh daily. Now, can we talk about lunch?  breakfast, coffee, espresso, latte, biscuits, sliders, bagel, granola, scone, fruit lunch, soup, bowl, humus, tuna, salads, cuban, sandwiches, cookie, chocolate chip, oatmeal eat in or takeout.
Drove from Western New York, was the best meal of the entire trip.  Great food and service.
Very cool space, friendly staff, good coffee!
Fresh soup, sandwiches, and great coffee.
Best spot in downtown for fresh baked breakfast and yummy lunch.
charming industrial/reclamation/retro architecture with reasonable prices and knowledgeable, friendly staff.  ~coffee newb
